@Reisenberger,

With the current design of IReadOnlyPolicyRegistry<in TKey>, we can't implement IEnumerable<KeyValuePair<TKey, ISPolicy>> as the T of IEnumerable is an out parameter and we are using TKey as an in.

Would it make sense to restrict the IReadOnlyPolicyRegistry to use a string. Is there any reason why someone would use another type as the key?
